
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `hostname` baraye namayesh ya tagheer daadane name computer shoma estefade mishavad. Name computer shoma rooye shabakeh baraye shenasaee estefade mishe.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `hostname` --> 🖥️ Namayesh dadane name fa'ali computer.
    🔹 `hostname -f` --> 🌐 Namayesh dadane name kamel domain (FQDN), agar computer be domain motasel bashe.
    🔹 `sudo hostname <name_jadid>` --> ✍️ Tagheer daadane name computer be <name_jadid> (niyaz be dastresi root darad).
    🔹 `hostname -i` --> 📍 Namayesh dadane address IP computer.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ hostname

    🔹 Namayesh name computer.

    $ hostname -f

    🔹 Namayesh name kamel domain agar mojood bashe.

    $ sudo hostname mynewhostname

    🔹 Tagheer dadane name computer be "mynewhostname" (motmaen shavid ke dastresi root darid).

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ hostname
    mycomputer

    🔹 Dastoor `hostname` sade name computer "mycomputer" ra namayesh midahad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `hostname` command is used to display or set the hostname of your computer. The hostname is used to identify your computer on a network.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `hostname` --> 🖥️ Display the current hostname.
    🔹 `hostname -f` --> 🌐 Display the fully qualified domain name (FQDN), if the computer is connected to a domain.
    🔹 `sudo hostname <new_hostname>` --> ✍️ Set the hostname to <new_hostname> (requires root access).
    🔹 `hostname -i` --> 📍 Display the IP address(es) of the hostname.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ hostname

    🔹 Display the hostname.

    $ hostname -f

    🔹 Display the FQDN if available.

    $ sudo hostname mynewhostname

    🔹 Change the hostname to "mynewhostname" (ensure you have root privileges).

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ hostname
    mycomputer

    🔹 The simple `hostname` command displays the computer's name, which is "mycomputer" in this case.
